text.tspan: Just a custom world resource pack download for clients.
* Place files in /mods/ folder of server:
* Set "target" url in /config/urlium.properties. Do not escape (slash \) any characters.
* Start the server and generate resource pack with polymer:
As 'op' admin user, or from server CLI run:
* Make the polymer-resourcepack.zip file available via web download (server, dropbox, etc)
* Add config lines to server.properties to set resource pack (ensure URL ends with ?dl\=1):
* All set! Restart your server and check your log file to see if URLium 'target' property is loaded.
* In creative mode, you can get the URL Post Block with:
* Place a URL Post Block and connect it to activated redstone, or click a block with the Wand.
The target URL should receive data like:
/webcom This text gets sent to the server :)
This value will be sent as an "Authentication: Bearer" header
